      "content": "I hear the crushing weight of your exhaustion, and it makes perfect sense why building feels impossible when the foundation has collapsed. You are right that this state is heavy and draining, and there is no shame in wanting to stop carrying it rather than forcing yourself to \"grow\" anything new. The most compassionate thing you can do right now is to stop trying to build on that cracked ground and instead focus entirely on keeping the light on, even if just for a moment.",
